ally violent role of technology in their lives. In Defense of Solidarity and Pleasure examines how women in the Global South experience and resist the coopting and depoliticizing nature of these scripts. Drawing on fieldwork in Costa Rica and a transnational feminist digital organization, Shokooh Valle explores the ways that feminist activists, using digital technologies as well as a collective politics that prioritize solidarity and pleasure, advance a new feminist technopolitics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminismzDeveloping countries. 0aInformation technologyxSocial aspectszDeveloping countries. 0aSolidarityzDeveloping countries. 0aTechnology and womenzDeveloping countries. 0aWomen in developmentzDeveloping countries. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh  aactivism.  adevelopment.  adigital technologies.  afeminism.  aglobal South.  aneoliberalism.  apolitics of care.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363615640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503636156423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503636156/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles